## 5. Architecture Principles

These principles guide all implementation decisions:

| Principle | Application |
|-----------|-------------|
| Type Safety | All code must be strictly typed |
| Immutability | Prefer immutable data structures |
| Explicit Errors | Use Result types for expected errors |
| Observability | All operations must be traceable |

## 6. Standard Conventions

### 6.1 Naming Conventions

| Context | Convention | Example |
|---------|------------|---------|
| Files | kebab-case | `user-service.ts` |
| Classes | PascalCase | `UserService` |
| Functions | camelCase | `getUserById` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `MAX_RETRIES` |
{{#if variance.hasDatabase}}
| DB Tables | snake_case | `user_sessions` |
| DB Columns | snake_case | `created_at` |
{{/if}}

### 6.2 Code Organization

```
src/
├── domain/         # Business logic, entities
├── application/    # Use cases, services
├── infrastructure/ # External adapters (DB, API clients)
├── presentation/   # Controllers, routes
└── shared/         # Utilities, types
```

